oc:kn_2e637699 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building DC-OPF problems for price extraction" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Store balance constraint references separately before solving so dual values can be extracted after optimization completes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "CVXPY dual values are only accessible on stored constraint objects; constraints embedded anonymously cannot yield LMPs." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_34623ed1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reading dual values from CVXPY constraints" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Check dual_value for None before scaling — solvers may not return duals if problem is infeasible or solver doesn't support dual extraction." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Graceful handling prevents crashes when optimization fails or solver doesn't populate dual information." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_53e4d68c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting LMPs from per-unit OPF formulations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Scale dual values by baseMVA to convert from per-unit to $/MWh: lmp = dual_value * baseMVA." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The power balance constraint is formulated in per-unit; multiplying by baseMVA converts shadow prices to actual $/MWh." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_77afd53a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When interpreting LMP results that contain negative values" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Negative LMPs are physically valid and expected in congested systems — they are not errors or solver artifacts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Negative LMPs occur when cheap generation is trapped behind a congested line; adding load at that bus relieves congestion by consuming local excess, reducing total system cost." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9a8183ce a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When identifying binding transmission constraints" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lines at or near thermal limits (≥99% loading) cause congestion and LMP separation across buses." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Binding lines are the physical cause of LMP differences between buses; identifying them explains the price structure." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d3d79225 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing counterfactual transmission analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Relaxing a binding constraint cannot increase system cost; cost reduction quantifies the shadow price of that constraint." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is the economic intuition behind congestion rent — the cost savings from relieving congestion measures the economic value of additional transmission capacity." .

